      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "At first, we confirmed a defective intracellular Zn 2+ signaling, besides previously shown Ca 2+ signaling  , in part, due to increased oxidative stress/depressed antioxidant defence in diabetic cardiomyocytes, with lower amplitude of Zn 2+ transients as well as markedly increased diastolic levels of both Zn 2+ and Ca 2+ since all these alterations could be prevented with either NAC treatment of diabetic rats or NAC-treatment of diabetic cardiomyocytes.",
